value.value: A human immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) monoclonal antibody targeting calcitonin gene-related peptide receptor (CGRPR), that can be used in the preventive treatment of migraine. Upon subcutaneous administration, erenumab specifically targets, binds to and blocks the activity of CGRPR. This may relief CGRPR-triggered migraine.
A family of serine proteases that catalyze the proteolytic conversion of plasminogen to plasmin.
A member of the serpin family of serine protease inhibitor proteins that inhibits plasminogen activator type proteases.
A phosphatidylcholine derivative that modulates inflammation, vascular permeability, allergic responses and the functions of leukocytes and platelets.
Any cell adhesion process that involves the association of platelets via adhesion molecules.
Having different forms at different stages of the life cycle.
